75-year-old Nyeri tycoon Stephen Wangondu accused of killing his son daniel Mwangi together with four of his co-accused have each been released on a 1 million shillings bond each. justice Florence muchemi ruled that the prosecution had failed to give enough evidence to show why the five should not be released on bail or bond wang'ondu, the main suspect, was however not present in court. he was represented by his lawyer who said that the accused was unwell and in hospital. the businessman is accused of hiring four hitmen, paying them a total of 160,000 shillings to eliminate his son